52 /**
53  * As all parameters are passed from hoc as double, we need
54  * to calculate max integer that can fit into double variable.
55  *
56  * With IEEE 64-bit double has 52 bits of mantissa, so it's 2^53.
57  * calculating it with approach `while (dbl + 1 != dbl) dbl++;`
58  * has issues with SSE and other 32 bits platform. So we are using
59  * direct value here.
60  *
61  * The maximum mantissa 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFF which is 52 bits all 1.
62  * In Python it's:
63  *
64  * >>> (2.**53).hex()
65  * '0x1.0000000000000p+53'
66  * >>> (2.**53)
67  * 9007199254740992.0
68  *
69  * See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1848700/biggest-integer-that-can-be-stored-in-a-double
70  */
71 static double dmaxint_ = 9007199254740992;

73 // Definitions allow machine independent write and read
74 // note that must include BYTEHEADER at head of routine
75 // The policy is that each machine vwrite binary information in
76 // without swapping, ie. native endian.
77 // On reading, the type is checked to decide whether
78 // byteswapping should be performed
79 
80 #define BYTEHEADER \
81  int _II__; \
82  char* _IN__; \
83  char _OUT__[16]; \
84  int BYTESWAP_FLAG = 0;
85 #define BYTESWAP(_X__, _TYPE__) \
86  if (BYTESWAP_FLAG == 1) { \
87  _IN__ = (char*) &(_X__); \
88  for (_II__ = 0; _II__ < sizeof(_TYPE__); _II__++) { \
89  _OUT__[_II__] = _IN__[sizeof(_TYPE__) - _II__ - 1]; \
90  } \
91  (_X__) = *((_TYPE__*) &_OUT__); \
92  }

201 /* the Vect->elem(start, end) function was used in about a dozen places
202 for the purpose of dealing with a subrange of elements. However that
203 function clones the subrange and returns a new Vect. This caused a
204 memory leak and was needlessly inefficient for those functions.
205 To fix both problems for these specific functions
206 we use a special vector which does not have
207 it's own space but merely a pointer and capacity to the right space of
208 the original vector. The usage is restricted to only once at a time, i.e.
209 can't use two subvecs at once and never do anything which affects the
210 memory space.
211 */

517 static double v_vwrite(void* v) {
518  Vect* vp = (Vect*) v;
519 
520  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
521  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
522  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
523 
524  FILE* fp = f->file();
525  if (!fp) {
526  return 0.;
527  }
528 
529  BinaryMode(f)
530  // first, write the size of the vector
531  int n = vp->size();
532  FWrite(&n, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
533 
534  // next, write the type of elements
535  int type = 4;
536  if (ifarg(2)) {
537  type = int(chkarg(2, 1, 5));
538  }
539  FWrite(&type, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
540 
541  // convert the data if necessary
542  int i;
543  void* s;
544  const char* x;
545 
546  double min, max, r, sf, sub, intermed;
547  switch (type) {
548  case 5: // integers as ints (no scaling)
549  {
550  int* xi = (int*) malloc(n * sizeof(int));
551  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
552  xi[i] = (int) (vp->elem(i));
553  }
554  FWrite(xi, sizeof(int), n, fp);
555  free((char*) xi);
556  break;
557  }
558 
559  case 4: // doubles (no conversion unless BYTESWAP used and needed)
560  {
561  s = (void*) (&(vp->elem(0)));
562  x = (const char*) s;
563  FWrite(x, sizeof(double), n, fp);
564  break;
565  }
566 
567  case 3: // float (simple automatic type conversion)
568  {
569  float* xf = (float*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(float));
570  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
571  xf[i] = float(vp->elem(i));
572  }
573  FWrite(xf, sizeof(float), n, fp);
574  free((char*) xf);
575  break;
576  }
577 
578 
579  case 2: // short ints (scale to 16 bits with compression)
580  {
581  auto minmax = std::minmax_element(vp->begin(), vp->end());
582  min = *minmax.first;
583  max = *minmax.second;
584  r = max - min;
585  if (r > 0) {
586  sf = TWO_BYTE_HIGH / r;
587  } else {
588  sf = 1.;
589  }
590  unsigned short* xi = (unsigned short*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(unsigned short));
591  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
592  intermed = (vp->elem(i) - min) * sf;
593  xi[i] = (unsigned short) intermed;
594  }
595  s = (void*) xi;
596  x = (const char*) s;
597  // store the info needed to reconvert
598  FWrite(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
599  FWrite(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
600  // store the actual data
601  FWrite(x, sizeof(unsigned short), n, fp);
602  free((char*) xi);
603  break;
604  }
605 
606  case 1: // char (scale to 8 bits with compression)
607  {
608  sub = ONE_BYTE_HALF;
609  auto minmax = std::minmax_element(vp->begin(), vp->end());
610  min = *minmax.first;
611  max = *minmax.second;
612  r = max - min;
613  if (r > 0) {
614  sf = ONE_BYTE_HIGH / r;
615  } else {
616  sf = 1.;
617  }
618 
619  char* xc = (char*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(char));
620  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
621  xc[i] = char(((vp->elem(i) - min) * sf) - sub);
622  }
623  s = (void*) xc;
624  x = (const char*) s;
625  // store the info needed to reconvert
626  FWrite(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
627  FWrite(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
628  FWrite(x, sizeof(char), n, fp);
629  free(xc);
630  break;
631  }
632  }
633  return 1;
634 }

637 static double v_vread(void* v) {
638  Vect* vp = (Vect*) v;
639  void* s = (void*) (vp->data());
640 
641  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
642  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
643  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
644  BYTEHEADER
645 
646  FILE* fp = f->file();
647  if (!fp) {
648  return 0.;
649  }
650 
651  BinaryMode(f) int n;
652  FRead(&n, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
653 
654  int type = 0;
655  FRead(&type, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
656 
657  // since the type ranges from 1 to 5 (very important that it not be 0)
658  // we can check the type and decide if it needs to be byteswapped
659  if (type < 1 || type > 5) {
660  BYTESWAP_FLAG = 1;
661  } else {
662  BYTESWAP_FLAG = 0;
663  }
664 
665  BYTESWAP(n, int)
666  BYTESWAP(type, int)
667  if (type < 1 || type > 5) {
668  return 0.;
669  }
670  if (vp->size() != n)
671  vp->resize(n);
672 
673  // read as appropriate type and convert to doubles
674 
675  int i;
676  double sf = 1.;
677  double min = 0.;
678  double add;
679 
680  switch (type) {
681  case 5: // ints; no conversion
682  {
683  int* xi = (int*) malloc(n * sizeof(int));
684  FRead(xi, sizeof(int), n, fp);
685  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
686  BYTESWAP(xi[i], int)
687  vp->elem(i) = double(xi[i]);
688  }
689  free((char*) xi);
690  break;
691  }
692 
693  case 4: // doubles
694  FRead(&(vp->elem(0)), sizeof(double), n, fp);
695  if (BYTESWAP_FLAG == 1) {
696  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
697  BYTESWAP(vp->elem(i), double)
698  }
699  }
700  break;
701 
702  case 3: // floats
703  {
704  float* xf = (float*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(float));
705  FRead(xf, sizeof(float), n, fp);
706  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
707  BYTESWAP(xf[i], float)
708  vp->elem(i) = double(xf[i]);
709  }
710  free((char*) xf);
711  break;
712  }
713 
714  case 2: // unsigned short ints
715  { // convert back to double
716  FRead(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
717  FRead(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
718  BYTESWAP(sf, double)
719  BYTESWAP(min, double)
720 
721  unsigned short* xi = (unsigned short*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(unsigned short));
722  FRead(xi, sizeof(unsigned short), n, fp);
723  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
724  BYTESWAP(xi[i], short)
725  vp->elem(i) = double(xi[i] / sf + min);
726  }
727  free((char*) xi);
728  break;
729  }
730 
731  case 1: // char
732  { // convert back to double
733  FRead(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
734  FRead(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
735  BYTESWAP(sf, double)
736  BYTESWAP(min, double)
737  char* xc = (char*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(char));
738  FRead(xc, sizeof(char), n, fp);
739  add = ONE_BYTE_HALF;
740  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
741  vp->elem(i) = double((xc[i] + add) / sf + min);
742  }
743  free(xc);
744  break;
745  }
746  }
747  return 1;
748 }

752  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;

754  int top = x->size() - 1;
755  int start = 0;
756  int end = top;
757  int next_arg = 1;

759  int print_file = 0;
760  int extra_newline = 1; // when no File
761  OcFile* f;

764  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);

766  f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
767  format = "%g\n";
768  next_arg++;
769  print_file = 1;

773  next_arg++;
774  extra_newline = 0;
775  }
776  if (ifarg(next_arg)) {

778  end = int(chkarg(next_arg + 1, start, top));

783  fprintf(f->file(), format, x->elem(i));
784  }
785  fprintf(f->file(), "\n");
786  } else {
787  for (int i = start; i <= end; i++) {
788  Printf(format, x->elem(i));
789  if (extra_newline && !((i - start + 1) % 5)) {

791  }

794  Printf("\n");
795  }
796  }

798  return double(end - start + 1);

802 static double v_scanf(void* v) {
803  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
804 
805  int n = -1;
806  int c = 1;
807  int nc = 1;
808  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
809  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
810  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
811 
812  hoc_return_type_code = 1; // integer
813 
814  if (ifarg(4)) {
815  n = int(*getarg(2));
816  c = int(*getarg(3));
817  nc = int(*getarg(4));
818  } else if (ifarg(3)) {
819  c = int(*getarg(2));
820  nc = int(*getarg(3));
821  } else if (ifarg(2)) {
822  n = int(*getarg(2));
823  }
824 
825  if (n >= 0) {
826  x->resize(n);
827  } else if (x->size()) { // gnuvec legacy handling
828  x->resize(0);
829  }
830 
831  // start at the right column
832 
833  int i = 0;
834 
835  while ((n < 0 || i < n) && !f->eof()) {
836  // skip unwanted columns before
837  int j;
838  for (j = 1; j < c; j++) {
839  if (!f->eof())
840  hoc_scan(f->file());
841  }
842 
843  // read data
844  if (!f->eof()) {
845  if (n >= 0)
846  x->elem(i) = hoc_scan(f->file());
847  else
848  x->push_back(hoc_scan(f->file()));
849  }
850 
851  // skip unwanted columns after
852  for (j = c; j < nc; j++) {
853  if (!f->eof())
854  hoc_scan(f->file());
855  }
856 
857  i++;
858  }
859 
860  if (x->size() != i)
861  x->resize(i);
862 
863  return double(i);
864 }

866 static double v_scantil(void* v) {
867  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
868  double val, til;
869 
870  int c = 1;
871  int nc = 1;
872  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
873  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
874  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
875  // old gnuvec compatibility: clear vector if not empty()
876  if (x->size() > 0) {
877  x->resize(0);
878  }
879 
880  hoc_return_type_code = 1; // integer
881  til = *getarg(2);
882  if (ifarg(4)) {
883  c = int(*getarg(3));
884  nc = int(*getarg(4));
885  }
886 
887  // start at the right column
888 
889  int i = 0;
890 
891  for (;;) {
892  // skip unwanted columns before
893  int j;
894  for (j = 1; j < c; j++) {
895  if (hoc_scan(f->file()) == til) {
896  return double(i);
897  }
898  }
899 
900  // read data
901  val = hoc_scan(f->file());
902  if (val == til) {
903  break;
904  }
905  x->push_back(val);
906 
907  // skip unwanted columns after
908  for (j = c; j < nc; j++) {
909  hoc_scan(f->file());
910  }
911 
912  i++;
913  }
914  return double(i);

1205 static Object** v_sumgauss(void* v) {
1206  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
1207 
1208  double low = *getarg(1);
1209  double high = chkarg(2, low, 1e99);
1210  double step = chkarg(3, 1.e-99, 1.e99);
1211  double var = chkarg(4, 0, 1.e99);
1212  Vect* w;
1213  bool d = false;
1214  if (ifarg(5)) {
1215  w = vector_arg(5);
1216  } else {
1217  w = new Vect(x->size());
1218  std::fill(w->begin(), w->end(), 1);
1219  d = true;
1220  }
1221 
1222  int points = int((high - low) / step + .5);
1223  Vect* sum = new Vect(points, 0.);
1224 
1225  double svar = var / (step * step);
1226 
1227  // 4/28/93 ZFM: corrected bug: replaced svar w/ var in line below
1228  double scale = 1. / hoc_Sqrt(2. * PI * var);
1229 
1230  for (int i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
1231  double xv = int((x->elem(i) - low) / step);
1232  for (int j = 0; j < points; j++) {
1233  double arg = -(j - xv) * (j - xv) / (2. * svar);
1234  if (arg > -20.)
1235  sum->elem(j) += hoc_Exp(arg) * scale * w->elem(i);
1236  }
1237  }
1238  if (d) {
1239  delete w;
1240  }
1241  return sum->temp_objvar();
1242 }

1244 static Object** v_smhist(void* v) {
1245  Vect* v1 = (Vect*) v;
1246 
1247  Vect* data = vector_arg(1);
1248 
1249  double start = *getarg(2);
1250  int size = int(*getarg(3));
1251  double step = chkarg(4, 1.e-99, 1.e99);
1252  double var = chkarg(5, 0, 1.e99);
1253 
1254  int weight, i;
1255  Vect* w;
1256 
1257  if (ifarg(6)) {
1258  w = vector_arg(6);
1259  if (w->size() != data->size()) {
1260  hoc_execerror("Vector.smhist: weight Vector must be same size as source Vector.", 0);
1261  }
1262  weight = 1;
1263  } else {
1264  weight = 0;
1265  }
1266 
1267 
1268  // ready a gaussian to convolve
1269  double svar = 2 * var / (step * step);
1270  double scale = 1 / hoc_Sqrt(2. * PI * var);
1271 
1272  int g2 = int(sqrt(10 * svar));
1273  int g = g2 * 2 + 1;
1274 
1275  int n = 1;
1276  while (n < size + g)
1277  n *= 2;
1278 
1279  double* gauss = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1280 
1281  for (i = 0; i <= g2; i++)
1282  gauss[i] = scale * hoc_Exp(-i * i / svar);
1283  for (i = 1; i <= g2; i++)
1284  gauss[g - i] = scale * hoc_Exp(-i * i / svar);
1285 
1286  // put the data into a time series
1287  double* series = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1288 
1289  double high = start + n * step;
1290  if (weight) {
1291  for (i = 0; i < data->size(); i++) {
1292  if (data->elem(i) >= start && data->elem(i) < high) {
1293  series[int((data->elem(i) - start) / step)] += w->elem(i);
1294  }
1295  }
1296  } else {
1297  for (i = 0; i < data->size(); i++) {
1298  if (data->elem(i) >= start && data->elem(i) < high) {
1299  series[int((data->elem(i) - start) / step)] += 1.;
1300  }
1301  }
1302  }
1303 
1304  // ready the answer vector
1305  double* ans = (double*) calloc(2 * n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1306 
1307  // convolve
1308  nrn_convlv(series, n, gauss, g, 1, ans);
1309 
1310  // put the answer in the vector
1311  if (v1->size() != size)
1312  v1->resize(size);
1313  std::fill(v1->begin(), v1->end(), 0.);
1314  for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
1315  if (ans[i] > EPSILON)
1316  v1->elem(i) = ans[i];
1317 
1318  free(series);
1319  free(gauss);
1320  free(ans);
1321 
1322  return v1->temp_objvar();
1323 }

1478 static Object** v_copy(void* v) {
1479  Vect* y = (Vect*) v;
1480 
1481  Vect* x = vector_arg(1);
1482 
1483  int top = x->size() - 1;
1484  int srcstart = 0;
1485  int srcend = top;
1486  int srcinc = 1;
1487 
1488  int deststart = 0;
1489  int destinc = 1;
1490 
1491  if (ifarg(2) && hoc_is_object_arg(2)) {
1492  Vect* srcind = vector_arg(2);
1493  int ns = srcind->size();
1494  int nx = x->size();
1495  if (ifarg(3)) {
1496  Vect* destind = vector_arg(3);
1497  if (destind->size() < ns) {
1498  ns = destind->size();
1499  }
1500  int ny = y->size();
1501  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
1502  int ix = (int) (srcind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1503  int iy = (int) (destind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1504  if (ix >= 0 && iy >= 0 && ix < nx && iy < ny) {
1505  y->elem(iy) = x->elem(ix);
1506  }
1507  }
1508  } else {
1509  if (y->size() < nx) {
1510  nx = y->size();
1511  }
1512  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
1513  int ii = (int) (srcind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1514  if (ii >= 0 && ii < nx) {
1515  y->elem(ii) = x->elem(ii);
1516  }
1517  }
1518  }
1519  return y->temp_objvar();
1520  }
1521 
1522  if (ifarg(2) && !(ifarg(3))) {
1523  deststart = int(*getarg(2));
1524  } else {
1525  if (ifarg(4)) {
1526  deststart = int(*getarg(2));
1527  srcstart = int(chkarg(3, 0, top));
1528  srcend = int(chkarg(4, -1, top));
1529  if (ifarg(5)) {
1530  destinc = int(chkarg(5, 1, dmaxint_));
1531  srcinc = int(chkarg(6, 1, dmaxint_));
1532  }
1533  } else if (ifarg(3)) {
1534  srcstart = int(chkarg(2, 0, top));
1535  srcend = int(chkarg(3, -1, top));
1536  }
1537  }
1538  if (srcend == -1) {
1539  srcend = top;
1540  } else if (srcend < srcstart) {
1541  hoc_execerror("Vector.copy: src_end arg smaller than src_start", 0);
1542  }
1543  int size = (srcend - srcstart) / srcinc;
1544  size *= destinc;
1545  size += deststart + 1;
1546  if (y->size() < size) {
1547  y->resize(size);
1548  } else if (y->size() > size && !ifarg(2)) {
1549  y->resize(size);
1550  }
1551  int i, j;
1552  for (i = srcstart, j = deststart; i <= srcend; i += srcinc, j += destinc) {
1553  y->elem(j) = x->elem(i);
1554  }
1555 
1556  return y->temp_objvar();
1557 }

1626 static Object** v_interpolate(void* v) {
1627  Vect* yd = (Vect*) v;
1628  Vect* xd = vector_arg(1);
1629  Vect* xs = vector_arg(2);
1630  Vect* ys;
1631  int flag, is, id, nd, ns;
1632  double thet;
1633  ns = xs->size();
1634  nd = xd->size();
1635  if (ifarg(3)) {
1636  ys = vector_arg(3);
1637  flag = 0;
1638  } else {
1639  ys = new Vect(*yd);
1640  flag = 1;
1641  }
1642  yd->resize(nd);
1643  // before domain
1644  for (id = 0; id < nd && xd->elem(id) <= xs->elem(0); ++id) {
1645  yd->elem(id) = ys->elem(0);
1646  }
1647  // in domain
1648  for (is = 1; is < ns && id < nd; ++is) {
1649  if (xs->elem(is) <= xs->elem(is - 1)) {
1650  continue;
1651  }
1652  while (xd->elem(id) <= xs->elem(is)) {
1653  thet = (xd->elem(id) - xs->elem(is - 1)) / (xs->elem(is) - xs->elem(is - 1));
1654  yd->elem(id) = (1. - thet) * (ys->elem(is - 1)) + thet * (ys->elem(is));
1655  ++id;
1656  if (id >= nd) {
1657  break;
1658  }
1659  }
1660  }
1661  // after domain
1662  for (; id < nd; ++id) {
1663  yd->elem(id) = ys->elem(ns - 1);
1664  }
1665 
1666  if (flag) {
1667  delete ys;
1668  }
1669  return yd->temp_objvar();
1670 }

1961 static Object** v_indgen(void* v) {
1962  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
1963 
1964  int n = x->size();
1965 
1966  double start = 0.;
1967  double step = 1.;
1968  double end = double(n - 1);
1969 
1970  if (ifarg(1)) {
1971  if (ifarg(3)) {
1972  start = *getarg(1);
1973  end = *getarg(2);
1974  step =
1975  chkarg(3, std::min(start - end, end - start), std::max(start - end, end - start));
1976  double xn = floor((end - start) / step + EPSILON) + 1.;
1977  if (xn > dmaxint_) {
1978  hoc_execerror("size too large", 0);
1979  } else if (xn < 0) {
1980  hoc_execerror("empty set", 0);
1981  }
1982  n = int(xn);
1983  if (n != x->size())
1984  x->resize(n);
1985  } else if (ifarg(2)) {
1986  start = *getarg(1);
1987  step = chkarg(2, -dmaxint_, dmaxint_);
1988  } else {
1989  step = chkarg(1, -dmaxint_, dmaxint_);
1990  }
1991  }
1992  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1993  x->elem(i) = double(i) * step + start;
1994  }
1995  return x->temp_objvar();

2409 /*=============================================================================
2410 
2411  FITTING A MULTIVARIABLE FUNCTION FROM DATA -- SIMPLEX METHOD
2412 
2413  double simplex( p,n,trial,a,b,c,d )
2414  double *p;
2415  vector of dimension n, containing variables
2416  int n;
2417  number of variables of the function to fit
2418  int trial;
2419  number of trials of simplex loop
2420  trial = 0: do simplex until the minimum pole has found
2421  trial > 0: do simplex [trial] times.
2422  double a,b,c,d
2423  values of contraction/expansion of the simplex;
2424  control the rate of the search in multidim variable space
2425  must be chosen by trial and error
2426  2.0, 1.4, 0.7, 0.3 -> standard values
2427 
2428  return most optimized eval value
2429  (negative if error occured)
2430 
2431  A function must be supplied by the user:
2432 
2433  external function DOUBLE EVAL(double *p);
2434 
2435  This function evaluates the mean square error between the
2436  the data and the multivariable function with the values of
2437  variables in vector p.
2438 
2439 =============================================================================*/
2440 
2441 
2442 #define SIMPLEX_MAXN 1e+300
2443 #define SIMPLEX_INORM 1.2
2444 
2445 /* 1.2: normal,
2446  1.3: extensive search,
2447  1.1: final adjustments
2448 */
2449 
2450 
2451 #define SIMPLEX_ALPHA 2.0
2452 #define SIMPLEX_BETA 1.4
2453 #define SIMPLEX_GAMMA 0.7
2454 #define SIMPLEX_DELTA 0.3
2455 
2456 /*
2457  values of contraction/expansion of the simplex;
2458  control the rate of the search in multidim variable space
2459  must be chosen by trial and error
2460  2.0, 1.4, 0.7, 0.3 -> standard values
2461 */
2462 
2463 static double splx_evl_;
2464 static int renew_;
2465 
2466 
2467 static double eval(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2468  double sq_err = 0.;
2469  double guess;
2470  int i;
2471  double dexp, t, amp1, tau1, amp2, tau2;
2472 
2473  if (!strcmp(fcn, "exp2")) {
2474  if (n < 4)
2475  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"exp2\") requires amp1,tau1,amp2,tau2");
2476  amp1 = p[0];
2477  tau1 = p[1];
2478  amp2 = p[2];
2479  tau2 = p[3];
2480 
2481  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2482  t = x->elem(i);
2483  dexp = amp1 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau1) + amp2 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau2);
2484  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2485  sq_err += guess * guess;
2486  }
2487  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "charging")) {
2488  if (n < 4)
2489  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"charging\") requires amp1,tau1,amp2,tau2");
2490  amp1 = p[0];
2491  tau1 = p[1];
2492  amp2 = p[2];
2493  tau2 = p[3];
2494 
2495  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2496  t = x->elem(i);
2497  dexp = amp1 * (1 - hoc_Exp(-t / tau1)) + amp2 * (1 - hoc_Exp(-t / tau2));
2498  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2499  sq_err += guess * guess;
2500  }
2501  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "exp1")) {
2502  if (n < 2)
2503  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"exp1\") requires amp,tau");
2504  amp1 = p[0];
2505  tau1 = p[1];
2506 
2507 
2508  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2509  t = x->elem(i);
2510  dexp = amp1 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau1);
2511  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2512  sq_err += guess * guess;
2513  }
2514  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "line")) {
2515  if (n < 2)
2516  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"line\") requires slope,intercept");
2517 
2518  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2519  guess = (p[0] * x->elem(i) + p[1]) - y->elem(i);
2520  sq_err += guess * guess;
2521  }
2522  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "quad")) {
2523  if (n < 3)
2524  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"quad\") requires ax^2+bx+c");
2525 
2526  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2527  guess = (p[0] * x->elem(i) * x->elem(i) + p[1] * x->elem(i) + p[2]) - y->elem(i);
2528  sq_err += guess * guess;
2529  }
2530  } else {
2531  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2532  // first the independent variable
2533  hoc_pushx(x->elem(i));
2534  // then other parameters
2535  for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
2536  hoc_pushx(p[j]);
2537 
2538  guess = hoc_call_func(hoc_lookup(fcn), n + 1) - y->elem(i);
2539  sq_err += guess * guess;
2540  }
2541  }
2542  return sq_err / x->size();
2543 }

2546 static double eval_error(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2547  double retval;
2548 
2549  if (renew_ > 3 * (n + 1)) {
2550  retval = eval(p, n, x, y, fcn);
2551  if (retval == splx_evl_)
2552  return (splx_evl_);
2553  else
2554  return (SIMPLEX_MAXN);
2555  } else {
2556  retval = eval(p, n, x, y, fcn);
2557  if (splx_evl_ > retval)
2558  splx_evl_ = retval;
2559  return (retval);
2560  }
2561 }

2563 static double simplex(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2564  int i, j;
2565  int emaxp; /* max position */
2566  int eminp;
2567  int ptr;
2568 
2569  double* evortex; /* eval value of votexes */
2570  double* gvortex; /* the vector of gravity */
2571  double* vortex; /* parameter matrix */
2572  double* nvortex; /* new vortex */
2573  double emax;
2574  double emin;
2575  double fv1;
2576 
2577  evortex = (double*) calloc(n + 1, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2578  gvortex = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2579  vortex = (double*) calloc(n * (n + 1), (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2580  nvortex = (double*) calloc(n * 4, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2581 
2582  if (0 == evortex || 0 == gvortex || 0 == vortex || 0 == nvortex) {
2583  Printf("allocation error in simplex()\n");
2584  nrn_exit(1);
2585  }
2586 
2587 
2588  // NEXT:;
2589  /* make the initial vortex matrix */
2590  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2591  for (j = 0; j < n; j++) {
2592  vortex[i * n + j] = p[j];
2593  if (i == j)
2594  vortex[i * n + j] *= SIMPLEX_INORM;
2595  }
2596  }
2597 
2598  /* evaluate the n+1 of vortexes and make the maximal one
2599  to be pointed out by emaxp */
2600  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++)
2601  evortex[i] = eval_error(&vortex[i * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2602 
2603 Label2:;
2604  emin = emax = evortex[0];
2605  emaxp = eminp = 0;
2606  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2607  fv1 = evortex[i];
2608  if (fv1 > emax) {
2609  emax = fv1;
2610  emaxp = i;
2611  }
2612  if (fv1 < emin) {
2613  emin = fv1;
2614  eminp = i;
2615  }
2616  }
2617  /* calculate the center of gravity */
2618  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2619  gvortex[i] = 0.0;
2620  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++)
2621  for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
2622  gvortex[j] += vortex[i * n + j];
2623  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2624  gvortex[i] = (gvortex[i] - vortex[emaxp * n + i]) / n;
2625 
2626  /* calculate the new vortexes */
2627 
2628  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2629  nvortex[i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_ALPHA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] + SIMPLEX_ALPHA * gvortex[i];
2630  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[0], n, x, y, fcn);
2631  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2632  ptr = 0;
2633  goto UPDATE;
2634  }
2635 
2636  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2637  nvortex[1 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_BETA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2638  SIMPLEX_BETA * gvortex[i];
2639  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[1 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2640  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2641  ptr = 1;
2642  goto UPDATE;
2643  }
2644 
2645  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2646  nvortex[2 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_GAMMA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2647  SIMPLEX_GAMMA * gvortex[i];
2648  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[2 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2649  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2650  ptr = 2;
2651  goto UPDATE;
2652  }
2653 
2654  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2655  nvortex[3 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_DELTA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2656  SIMPLEX_DELTA * gvortex[i];
2657  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[3 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2658  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2659  ptr = 3;
2660  goto UPDATE;
2661  }
2662 
2663  goto Label3;
2664 
2665 
2666 UPDATE:;
2667  /* update the vortex matrix */
2668  if (splx_evl_ == fv1)
2669  renew_++;
2670  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2671  vortex[emaxp * n + i] = nvortex[ptr * n + i];
2672  evortex[emaxp] = fv1;
2673  goto Label2;
2674 
2675 
2676 Label3:;
2677  /*
2678  ** search for the vortex that represents smallest eval vaule
2679  */
2680  emin = evortex[0];
2681  eminp = 0;
2682  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2683  if (evortex[i] < emin) {
2684  emin = evortex[i];
2685  eminp = i;
2686  }
2687  }
2688 
2689  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2690  p[i] = vortex[eminp * n + i];
2691  free(gvortex);
2692  free(evortex);
2693  free(vortex);
2694  free(nvortex);
2695  return (emin);
2696 }

3281  }

3426 static Object** v_psth(void* v) {
3427  Vect* ans = (Vect*) v;
3428 
3429  // data set
3430  Vect* v1 = vector_arg(1);
3431 
3432  double dt = chkarg(2, 0, 9e99);
3433  double trials = chkarg(3, 0, 9e99);
3434  double size = chkarg(4, 0, v1->size() / 2);
3435  int n = int(v1->size());
3436 
3437  Vect* temp = new Vect(n);
3438 
3439  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3440  int fj = 0;
3441  int bj = 0;
3442  double integral = v1->elem(i);
3443  while (integral < size) {
3444  if (i + fj < n - 1) {
3445  fj++;
3446  integral += v1->elem(i + fj);
3447  }
3448  if (i - bj > 0 && integral < size) {
3449  bj++;
3450  integral += v1->elem(i - bj);
3451  }
3452  }
3453  temp->elem(i) = integral / trials * 1000. / ((fj + bj + 1) * dt);
3454  }
3455 
3456  ans->vec().swap(temp->vec());
3457 
3458  delete temp;
3459 
3460  return ans->temp_objvar();
3461 }

3463 static Object** v_inf(void* x) {
3464  Vect* V = (Vect*) x;
3465 
3466  // data set
3467  Vect* stim = vector_arg(1);
3468  int n = stim->size();
3469 
3470  double dt = chkarg(2, 1e-99, 9e99);
3471  double gl = *getarg(3);
3472  double el = *getarg(4);
3473  double cm = *getarg(5) / dt;
3474  double th = *getarg(6);
3475  double res = *getarg(7);
3476  double refp = 0;
3477  if (ifarg(8))
3478  refp = *getarg(8);
3479 
3480  if (V->size() != n)
3481  V->resize(n);
3482 
3483  double i = 0, v, ref = 0;
3484 
3485  V->elem(0) = el;
3486 
3487  for (int t = 0; t < n - 1; t++) {
3488  i = -gl * (V->elem(t) - el) + stim->elem(t);
3489  v = V->elem(t) + i / cm;
3490  if (v >= th && ref <= 0) {
3491  V->elem(t + 1) = 0;
3492  t = t + 1;
3493  V->elem(t + 1) = res;
3494  ref = refp;
3495  } else {
3496  ref = ref - dt;
3497  V->elem(t + 1) = v;
3498  }
3499  }
3500  return V->temp_objvar();

3503 static Object** v_pow(void* v) {
3504  Vect* ans = (Vect*) v;
3505  Vect* v1;
3506  int iarg = 1;
3507 
3508  // data set
3509  if (hoc_is_object_arg(iarg)) {
3510  v1 = vector_arg(iarg++);
3511  } else {
3512  v1 = ans;

3539  }
3540  } else if (p == 2) {
3541  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3542  ans->elem(i) = v1->elem(i) * v1->elem(i);
3543  }
3544  } else {
3545  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3546  ans->elem(i) = pow(v1->elem(i), p);
